
---

@startuml
' Class Diagram for Kinepolis Cinema System

class Cinema {
  +String name
  +List<Theatre> theatres
  +List<MovieCopy> movieCopies
}

class Theatre {
  +String id
  +String name
  +int capacity
  +List<Show> shows
}

class Movie {
  +String title
  +String genre
  +int duration
}

class MovieCopy {
  +String id
  +Movie movie
  +Cinema currentCinema
}

class Show {
  +String id
  +DateTime startTime
  +DateTime endTime
  +Theatre theatre
  +Movie movie
  +List<SeatReservation> reservations
  +boolean published
}

class SeatReservation {
  +String id
  +Customer customer
  +Show show
  +Seat seat
  +DateTime reservationTime
  +boolean cancelled
}

class Customer {
  +String id
  +String name
  +String email
  +String creditCardNumber
}

class Offer {
  +String id
  +Show originalShow
  +Show newShow
  +DateTime expirationTime
  +boolean accepted
}

class Ticket {
  +String id
  +Customer customer
  +Show show
  +Seat seat
  +boolean isReserved
  +boolean isAnonymous
}

class Seat {
  +String id
  +Theatre theatre
  +boolean isAvailable
}

' Relationships

Cinema "1" -- "0..*" Theatre: has
Theatre "1" -- "1" Show: has
Show "1" -- "1" Movie: uses
Show "1" -- "1" Theatre: located in
Movie "1" -- "0..*" MovieCopy: has
MovieCopy "1" -- "1" Cinema: belongs to
Show "1" -- "0..*" SeatReservation: has
Customer "1" -- "0..*" SeatReservation: made by
Show "1" -- "0..*" Offer: related to
Show "1" -- "0..*" Ticket: issued for
Theatre "1" -- "0..*" Seat: has
Seat "1" -- "0..*" Show: assigned to

@enduml

---

### Notes:
- The diagram captures all the entities and relationships described in the system requirement.
- `Show` is linked to both a `Theatre` and a `Movie`, indicating that it is a program of a specific movie in a specific theatre.
- `SeatReservation` is tied to a `Customer`, a `Show`, and a `Seat`.
- `Offer` is created when a `Show` is cancelled and offers a new seat in another theatre.
- `Ticket` can be either reserved or anonymous (for walk-ins), and is linked to a `Show`.

